From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: robert-brunson-fragile <siinspam@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 21 Jun 2026 01:25:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 15/15] fix(streaming): don't emit content as
 reasoning.available when structured reasoning exists
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Models like GLM-5.2 return reasoning in a separate reasoning_content field
alongside a visible content preamble. The conversation loop was firing
reasoning.available with the visible content text, causing it to appear in
both the main content panel (via assistant.delta streaming) and the thinking
panel (via tool.progress events) during live streaming — duplicating the
content. After session refresh the persisted message rendered correctly
because content and reasoning_content are stored separately.

Fix: skip the content-as-reasoning fallback when the model returned
structured reasoning fields (reasoning_content, reasoning, reasoning_details).
The fallback is only intended for models that embed <think> tags inline
in their content without separate API fields.

Co-authored-by: Nako <280596805+nakoagent@users.noreply.github.com>

diff --git a/agent/conversation_loop.py b/agent/conversation_loop.py
index ea5cb6f9e..57b986659 100644
--- a/agent/conversation_loop.py
+++ b/agent/conversation_loop.py
@@ -3725,7 +3725,26 @@ def run_conversation(
 
             # Notify progress callback of model's thinking (used by subagent
             # delegation to relay the child's reasoning to the parent display).
-            if (assistant_message.content and agent.tool_progress_callback):
+            #
+            # Skip this content-as-reasoning fallback when the model returned
+            # structured reasoning (reasoning_content / reasoning /
+            # reasoning_details).  In that case the visible content is a
+            # normal assistant message that was already streamed via
+            # assistant.delta events — firing it as reasoning.available
+            # duplicates it in the thinking panel during live streaming.
+            # The actual structured reasoning is either streamed via
+            # _fire_reasoning_delta (when reasoning_callback is wired) or
+            # persisted for post-refresh display.
+            _has_structured_reasoning = bool(
+                getattr(assistant_message, 'reasoning_content', None)
+                or getattr(assistant_message, 'reasoning', None)
+                or getattr(assistant_message, 'reasoning_details', None)
+            )
+            if (
+                assistant_message.content
+                and agent.tool_progress_callback
+                and not _has_structured_reasoning
+            ):
                 _think_text = assistant_message.content.strip()
                 # Strip reasoning XML tags that shouldn't leak to parent display
                 _think_text = re.sub(
